examples.en: The youngest son was sent out to Canada.
He will be the youngest runner in the race.
If I had to make a guess, I'd say Sam was the youngest.
Our youngest daughter just started school.
Our youngest child, Sam, has just started university.
They had to institutionalize their youngest son.
He became the youngest titleholder in the sport's history.
Tradition dictates that the youngest member should go first.
The youngest son has only brought down trouble on the family.
The youngest son was bound to a master builder for seven years.
Jonah and his youngest son were, on the surface at least, reconciled.
They are the youngest children in modern times to face murder charges.
The family were so ashamed when the youngest son was expelled from his school.
The family were so ashamed of the youngest son that they bundled him off to Canada.
My youngest boy has not left my side (=has stayed near me) since his daddy was killed.
